    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-05-07T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-05-07T11:00:00-05:00" n="248"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d248">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">560.AL/5–749: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chairman of the United States Delegation</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Willoughby</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Annecy</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-05-07T17:00:00+01:00"
                            >May 7, 1949—5 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Unnumbered. <gloss target="#t_USDel1">USDel</gloss> will shortly receive details
                    new South Africa import restrictions for consultation under relevant provisions
                        <gloss target="#t_GATT1">GATT</gloss>. Please telegraph immediately any
                    useful information, particularly on need for South Africa discrimination against
                    hard currency imports. Also available info on current <gloss target="#t_IMF1"
                        >IMF</gloss> discussions with South Africa.</p>
                <p>Passed to Capetown as number 1.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Willoughby</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
